Copy file to HDFS. Run hadoop fs –copyFromLocal words.txt to copy the text file to HDFS.
Verify file was copied to HDFS. Run hadoop fs –ls to verify the file was copied to HDFS.
Copy a file within HDFS. You can make a copy of a file in HDFS. Run hadoop fs -cp words.txt words2.txt to make a copy of words.txt called words2.txt
Copy a file from HDFS. We can also copy a file from HDFS to the local file system. Run hadoop fs -copyToLocal words2.txt . to copy words2.txt to the local directory.
Delete a file in HDFS. Let's the delete words2.txt in HDFS. Run hadoop fs -rm words2.txt
